You can add items in bulk, by *unpacking* the queryset, and then thus add all these elements in a single [&lt;b&gt;&lt;code&gt;.add(&amp;hellip;)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/b&gt; [Django-doc]](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/models/relations/#django.db.models.fields.related.RelatedManager.add) call:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;my_user.groups.add(&lt;b&gt;*&lt;/b&gt;my_group_queryset)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

Notice the asterisk (`*`) in the front. This will thus unpack the queryset, and pass each item as an individual parameter to the &lt;code&gt;.add(&amp;hellip;)&lt;/code&gt; function.

